aws::graph::propositions: # Meteorological Information and Flight Plan for Accident
The accident site had Visual Meteorological Conditions (VMC).
The condition of light at the accident site was Day.
The observation facility was PSP.
PSP is located at an elevation of 477 feet mean sea level.
The observation time was 10:53 Local.
The lowest cloud condition was at 20000 feet Above Ground Level.
The lowest ceiling was Broken at 20000 feet Above Ground Level.
The wind speed was 4 knots.
The altimeter setting was 30.2 inches of mercury.
There was no obscuration at the accident site.
There was no precipitation at the accident site.
The departure point was Palm Springs, California (PSP).
The destination was CYBW.
The departure time was 10:52 Local.
At 10:52, the Palm Springs (PSP) automated weather reporting facility indicated wind was calm.
At 10:52, the Palm Springs (PSP) automated weather reporting facility indicated visibility was 45 miles.
At 10:52, the Palm Springs (PSP) automated weather reporting facility indicated the sky was clear.
At 10:52, the Palm Springs (PSP) automated weather reporting facility indicated the temperature was 19 degrees Celsius.
At 10:52, the Palm Springs (PSP) automated weather reporting facility indicated the dew point was 10 degrees Celsius.
At 10:52, the Palm Springs (PSP) automated weather reporting facility indicated the altimeter setting was 30.08 inches of mercury.

text:
# Meteorological Information and Flight Plan

## Conditions at Accident Site:
| Condition | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Visual (VMC) | Condition of Light: Day |
| Observation Facility, Elevation: | PSP,477 ft msl |
| Observation Time: | 10:53 Local |
| Lowest Cloud Condition: | 20000 ft AGL |
| Lowest Ceiling: | Broken / 20000 ft AGL |
| Wind Speed/Gusts: | 4 knots / |
| Wind Direction: |  |
| Altimeter Setting: | 30.2 inches Hg |
| Precipitation and Obscuration: | No Obscuration; No Precipitation |
| Departure Point: | Palm Springs, CA (PSP ) |
| Destination: | (CYBW) |
| Departure Time: | 10:52 Local |

At 1052, the PSP automated weather reporting facility indicated wind calm, visibility 45 miles, sky clear, temperature 19C, dew point 10C, and an altimeter setting of 30.08 inches of mercury.
